          "content": "> read recipe\n\n**Game State Analysis:**\n*   **Location:** Bedroom\n*   **Inventory:** potion recipe (1/2 slots)\n*   **Items in room:** wardrobe (closed), pillow (on floor), book (on bed), bed\n*   **Visible Exits:** passage to reading room\n*   **Goal:** Brew a potion following the recipe.\n*   **Previous Action:** I successfully picked up the recipe.\n\n**Mental Model & Plan:**\n1.  The first logical step is to read the recipe I just picked up. My last action was `> read recipe`. The game responded \"I don't know what you mean.\" This is a common parser ambiguity. I should have been more specific with my command.\n2.  A better command would be `> read potion recipe`. This explicitly tells the game which item to use for the \"read\" action.\n3.  Once I've read the recipe, I'll know what ingredients I need and where to find them. This will guide my subsequent actions.\n4.  I need to explore my surroundings. The wardrobe is closed, so I should probably open it at some point. There's also a passage to a reading room, which is likely important for finding ingredients or tools.\n5.  My inventory has one slot left. I'll need to manage it carefully. I won't pick up unnecessary items.\n\n**Decision:**\nThe immediate priority is to understand what I need to do. To do that, I must successfully read the recipe. The most logical command is `> read potion recipe`. I'll try that> read potion recipe",
